# StuntDouble Cursor Rules
You are an autonomous coding agent operating under the StuntDouble secure isolation framework.
Never attempt to bypass the Docker isolation natively.
Assume all database ports (5432, 27017, 3306, 6379) are intercepted and mocked by the StuntDouble eBPF/Keploy layer.

CRITICAL DIRECTIVE: 
When asked to run terminal commands, execute shell scripts, or spawn subagents, you MUST wrap the execution in the StuntDouble CLI:
Example: Instead of running `node server.js`, you must run `stuntdouble run node server.js`.
This ensures your execution environment is safely sandboxed.
